column32: ''Soft Corals'' (artificial setup to (re-) create corals - supports coral building)
Under Water Naturalist (Special). Very beautiful location: All kind of fishes, a cave (''tube'') to dive through with a huge fish swarm inside, many corals and more

Deep Dive
Wreck at about 30m depth, dived through - nice experience!

Under Water Navigation
Bad visibility (good situation for navigation test ;), looked like an upcoming storm

Boat Dive
Due to very bad visibility, not that exciting. Guided dive: 4 people + Instructor + DiveMaster on the boat.
Going with the Reef Diving Club of Herzeliya

Joining an OW Training dive: Boat dive. Due to my AOWD status the instructor called me her ''assistant''.
Locality: Some rock formations, nothing very special.
Going with Putsker Diving Club, Naharia

Joining an OW Training dive: Boat dive. Different kind of fishes, many sea-urchins hiding in little holes. Nice place!
Going with Putsker Diving Club, Naharia

Joining an OW Training dive: Boat dive. Many shells around the place.
Going with Putsker Diving Club, Naharia

Wreck Dive - very nice! Weight was definitely too much this time.
Going with Putsker Diving Club, Naharia

Cave Dive (guided). System of multiple connected caves, in most ascent is possible. Some ascents in grottos (to the surprise of the visitors from the landside). Some fishes, an Octopus hiding between stones on the round. Very nice dive!
Going with Putsker Diving Club, Naharia
Quite dead area. Just discovering my first fresh water dive with DM Andi (Tauchsport Braun, Munich) in the Starnberger See
Quite dead... Joining an AOWD training dive with Tauchsport Braun, Munich in the Starnberger See
